targeting support for Windows Sun Valley 2, as well as adding several improvements in the process.\n                    - heading \"New features\" [level=1] [ref=e752]\n                    - list [ref=e753]:\n                      - listitem [ref=e754]:\n                        - strong [ref=e755]: Localization support\n                        - text: TranslucentTB can now be localized in different languages. Take a look at the\n                        - link \"contributor's guide\" [ref=e756] [cursor=pointer]:\n                          - /url: https://github.com/TranslucentTB/TranslucentTB/blob/release/CONTRIBUTING.md\n                        - text: \"if you want to submit your own translation! Currently supported languages are:\"\n                        - list [ref=e757]:\n                          - listitem [ref=e758]: Chinese (Simplified)\n                          - listitem [ref=e759]: Chinese (Traditional)\n                          - listitem [ref=e760]: Japanese\n                          - listitem [ref=e761]: English (United States)\n                      - listitem [ref=e762]:\n                        - strong [ref=e763]: Portable mode\n                        - text: On Windows 11, TranslucentTB can now run without needing to be installed.\n                        - link \"Download the TranslucentTB-portable-x64.zip file below\" [ref=e764] [cursor=pointer]:\n                          - /url: https://github.com/TranslucentTB/TranslucentTB/releases/download/2022.1/TranslucentTB-portable-x64.zip\n                          - text: Download the\n                          - code [ref=e765]: TranslucentTB-portable-x64.zip\n                          - text: file below\n                        - text: to get started.\n                      - listitem [ref=e766]:\n                        - strong [ref=e767]: Rules\n                        - text: \"Exposed in the configuration file only, rules allow you to customize the taskbar's appearance in a per-app manner: depending on the highest Z-order maximized window or the currently active window.\"\n                      - listitem [ref=e768]:\n                        - strong [ref=e769]: Remove the taskbar line/border\n                        - text: On Windows 11, you can now remove the taskbar line or border depending on which state is active.\n                    - heading \"Bug fixes\" [level=1] [ref=e770]\n                    - list [ref=e771]:\n                      - listitem [ref=e772]: Fix battery saver mode being active despite the user having disabled it.\n                      - listitem [ref=e773]: Made some changes that should significantly help with TranslucentTB not working after the computer resumes from sleep or when a display is unplugged or plugged in.\n                      - listitem [ref=e774]: Fix poor tray icon contrast in high contrast modes like \"Desert\".\n                      - listitem [ref=e775]: Hide empty document errors when the configuration file is empty.\n                      - listitem [ref=e776]: Fix tray icon turning blurry when the system DPI changes.\n                      - listitem [ref=e777]: Fix search opened and Start opened states on Windows 11.\n                      - listitem [ref=e778]: Fix an issue where TranslucentTB's settings could end up being wiped when shutting down the computer.\n                      - listitem [ref=e779]: Fix TranslucentTB crashing if you uninstall it while the welcome dialog is open.\n                    - heading \"Various improvements/changes\" [level=1] [ref=e780]\n                    - list [ref=e781]:\n                      - listitem [ref=e782]: Allow blur to be picked again on Windows 11 RTM when KB5006746 is installed.\n                      - listitem [ref=e783]: Remove blur on Windows 11 SV2. This feature has been removed from the OS by Microsoft. It's likely not coming back.\n                      - listitem [ref=e784]: When blur is not available on the user's system, automatically upgrade them to acrylic.\n                      - listitem [ref=e785]: Enable XAML context menu on Windows 10 build 19041-19045 if KB5007253 is installed.\n                      - listitem [ref=e786]: Update WinUI to 2.8.\n                      - listitem [ref=e787]: Use the new Segoe UI Variable font on Windows 11 for XAML UI elements.\n                      - listitem [ref=e788]: Various code cleanups and modernization.\n                    - separator [ref=e789]\n                    - paragraph [ref=e790]:\n                      - text: As always, you can download this release from the\n                      - link \"Microsoft Store\" [ref=e791] [cursor=pointer]:\n                        - /url: https://www.microsoft.com/store/apps/9PF4KZ2VN4W9\n                      - text: \", or by\"\n                      - link \"downloading and opening the TranslucentTB.appinstaller file below\" [ref=e792] [cursor=pointer]:\n                        - /url: https://github.com/TranslucentTB/TranslucentTB/releases/download/2022.1/TranslucentTB.appinstaller\n                        - text: downloading and opening the\n                        - code [ref=e793]: TranslucentTB.appinstaller\n                        - text: file below\n                      - text: . Additionally, Windows 11 users can download the portable version by\n                      - link \"downloading TranslucentTB-portable-x64.zip\" [ref=e794] [cursor=pointer]:\n                        - /url: https://github.com/TranslucentTB/TranslucentTB/releases/download/2022.1/TranslucentTB-portable-x64.zip\n                        - text: downloading\n                        - code [ref=e795]: TranslucentTB-portable-x64.zip\n                      - text: .\n                - generic [ref=e796]:\n                  - group [ref=e799]:\n                    - button \"Assets 14\" [ref=e800] [cursor=pointer]:\n                      - generic [ref=e801]:\n                        - generic [ref=e802]: Assets\n              